This paper deals with network protocols and their interoperability, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses automated software testing techniques, such as Symbolic Execution (SymEx), which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the need for implementations to provide additional information about their current protocol state, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the bugs found in the case study, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
